## CSS Custom Properties as Design Tokens

```css
/* tokens.css */
:root {
  /* Color palette */
  --color-brand-500: oklch(58% 0.22 250);
  --color-brand-600: oklch(50% 0.22 250);
  --color-surface: oklch(98% 0 0);
  --color-surface-raised: oklch(96% 0 0);
  --color-text: oklch(18% 0 0);
  --color-text-muted: oklch(50% 0 0);

  /* Spacing scale (4px base) */
  --space-1: 0.25rem;
  --space-2: 0.5rem;
  --space-4: 1rem;
  --space-8: 2rem;
  --space-16: 4rem;

  /* Typography */
  --text-sm: clamp(0.8rem, 0.75rem + 0.25vw, 0.875rem);
  --text-base: clamp(1rem, 0.92rem + 0.4vw, 1.125rem);
  --text-lg: clamp(1.25rem, 1.1rem + 0.75vw, 1.5rem);
  --text-xl: clamp(1.5rem, 1.2rem + 1.5vw, 2.25rem);
  --text-hero: clamp(2.5rem, 1.5rem + 5vw, 5rem);

  /* Motion */
  --duration-fast: 120ms;
  --duration-normal: 250ms;
  --ease-out: cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
}

/* Dark mode override */
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  :root {
    --color-surface: oklch(14% 0 0);
    --color-text: oklch(92% 0 0);
  }
}
```

**Rules:**
- Tokens are the ONLY source of color, spacing, type â€” never hardcode hex/px in component CSS
- Use `oklch()` for perceptually uniform colors and easy manipulation
- Use `clamp()` for fluid scaling â€” no breakpoint-based font sizes
- Dark mode is a one-line token swap, not a separate stylesheet

## CSS Grid Layout Patterns

### Page shell with named areas
```css
.layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 240px 1fr;
  grid-template-rows: auto 1fr auto;
  grid-template-areas:
    "header header"
    "nav    main"
    "footer footer";
  min-height: 100dvh;
}

.layout > header { grid-area: header; }
.layout > nav    { grid-area: nav; }
.layout > main   { grid-area: main; }
.layout > footer { grid-area: footer; }

@media (width < 768px) {
  .layout {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    grid-template-areas: "header" "main" "nav" "footer";
  }
}
```

### Auto-fill responsive card grid
```css
.card-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(min(280px, 100%), 1fr));
  gap: var(--space-4);
}
```

### Holy grail with subgrid
```css
.card-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr));
  grid-template-rows: auto;
}

.card {
  display: grid;
  grid-row: span 3;
  grid-template-rows: subgrid; /* align card internals across row */
}
```

**Rules:**
- Use `auto-fill` + `minmax` for self-adapting grids â€” no media queries needed
- Name areas with `grid-template-areas` when you have more than 2 regions
- Prefer `gap` over margin between grid children
- `min(280px, 100%)` prevents overflow on small viewports

## CSS Flexbox Patterns

### Navigation bar (space-between)
```css
.nav {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  gap: var(--space-4);
  padding-inline: var(--space-8);
}

/* Push last item to end */
.nav > .actions { margin-inline-start: auto; }
```

### Perfect centering
```css
.center {
  display: flex;
  place-items: center; /* shorthand for align + justify */
  min-height: 100dvh;
}
```

### Stretch card in a row
```css
.row { display: flex; gap: var(--space-4); }
.row > * { flex: 1 1 0; } /* equal width, can shrink, no intrinsic basis */
```

### Wrap with consistent item size
```css
.tag-list {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: var(--space-2);
}
.tag-list > * { flex: 0 0 auto; }
```

**Grid vs Flex decision:**
- Two dimensions (rows AND columns) â†’ Grid
- One dimension OR content-driven sizing â†’ Flexbox
- Alignment within a grid cell â†’ nested Flexbox inside Grid

## CSS Animations â€” Compositor-Only Properties

### Good â€” GPU-composited
```css
.card {
  transition: transform var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-out),
              opacity var(--duration-fast) ease;
  will-change: transform; /* hint for dedicated layer â€” remove after animation */
}

.card:hover {
  transform: translateY(-4px) scale(1.01);
  opacity: 0.95;
}
```

### Reveal animation with @keyframes
```css
@keyframes slide-up {
  from { transform: translateY(1rem); opacity: 0; }
  to   { transform: translateY(0);    opacity: 1; }
}

.hero-text {
  animation: slide-up 0.5s var(--ease-out) both;
}
```

### Reduced motion respect
```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *, *::before, *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

**Never animate (causes layout/paint):**
- `width`, `height`, `margin`, `padding` â†’ use `transform: scale()` instead
- `top`, `left` â†’ use `transform: translate()` instead
- `font-size` â†’ animate with `transform: scale()` on a wrapper
- `background-color` â†’ acceptable only for short durations

## CSS Container Queries

```css
/* 1. Declare the containment context */
.card-wrapper {
  container-type: inline-size;
  container-name: card;
}

/* 2. Query the container, not the viewport */
@container card (width >= 480px) {
  .card {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
  }
}

@container card (width < 480px) {
  .card-image { aspect-ratio: 16/9; width: 100%; }
}
```

### Container units
```css
.card-title {
  font-size: clamp(1rem, 5cqi, 1.5rem); /* cqi = 1% of container inline-size */
}
```

**Why this beats media queries for components:**
- A `.card` in a 3-column grid vs full-width both render correctly
- Zero coupling between component and page layout
- Composable: nest containers, each responds independently

**Support:** Baseline 2023 â€” all major browsers. Safe to use.

## CSS Logical Properties

```css
/* Physical â†’ Logical equivalents */
margin-left:   â†’ margin-inline-start
margin-right:  â†’ margin-inline-end
margin-top:    â†’ margin-block-start
padding-left:  â†’ padding-inline-start
border-left:   â†’ border-inline-start
width:         â†’ inline-size
height:        â†’ block-size
top:           â†’ inset-block-start
left:          â†’ inset-inline-start

/* Shorthand logical properties */
.component {
  margin-inline: auto;         /* left+right = auto */
  padding-inline: var(--space-4);
  padding-block: var(--space-2);
  inset-inline: 0;             /* left: 0; right: 0 */
  border-inline-start: 3px solid var(--color-brand-500);
}
```

**Rule:** All new CSS must use logical properties. Physical direction properties are banned in shared components.

## CSS @layer Cascade Architecture

```css
/* Define layer order at the top of your root stylesheet â€” lower = lower priority */
@layer reset, tokens, base, components, utilities;

@layer reset {
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; }
  body { margin: 0; }
  img { max-inline-size: 100%; display: block; }
}

@layer tokens {
  :root { --color-brand: oklch(58% 0.22 250); }
}

@layer base {
  body { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; color: var(--color-text); }
  a { color: var(--color-brand); }
}

@layer components {
  .btn {
    padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-4);
    background: var(--color-brand);
  }
}

@layer utilities {
  .sr-only { position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; overflow: hidden; clip: rect(0 0 0 0); }
  .visually-hidden { composes: sr-only; }
}
```

**Benefits:**
- Any class in `utilities` beats `components` regardless of selector specificity
- Third-party CSS imported into a lower layer can't leak specificity into your components
- Eliminates `!important` hacks
